I don't think he meant that you would have exclusive rights to a mob even if you don't have an adequate force to kill the mob in question. I think what he was getting at is that it's wrong for people to mess with a spawn cycle that someone else starts (Rhag1/Rhag2/AL or SoRZ/Idol/AoW, etc) unless they wipe, have no intentions of completing the cycle, or leave. Like if GUILD_A has say 30-40 people in SSRA and they buff, clear and kill Rhag1, GUILD_B has no right to touch Rhag 2 or AL that GUILD_A spawned unless for some reason GUILD_A isn't going to kill them, GUILD_A leaves or GUILD_A wipes. If GUILD_B hangs around to see if GUILD_A succeeds with AL or not, then GUILD_A wipes and GUILD_B takes AL at 100% and succeeds, it would be fair game. <br>
